-- Shares in Banca Carige up 4 pct as gets closer to asset sale
-- By Francesca Landini
-- Fri Jul 25, 2014 03:13AM EDT
-- None



MILAN, July 25 (Reuters) - Shares in Banca Carige <CRGI.MI> rose more than 4 percent in early trading on Friday after the Italian mid-sized lender said it was getting closer to the sale of its insurance units, a move that would boost its core capital.

The Genoa-based lender said late on Thursday it had entered exclusive talks with U.S. investment fund Apollo Management Holdings LP for the sale of its Carige Vita Nuova and Carige Assicurazioni. [ID:nL6N0PZ640] Carige is one of 15 Italian banks seeking to pass a regulatory health check of lenders across the euro zone.